text:
Stayed here for 4-nights for a conference in BNDCC. Basically the site has two properties: Renaissance and Marriott’s Vacation Club Nusa Dua Terrace. Both shares the same facilities it’s just MVC is more catered to vila type of room while Renaissance is a standard hotel room.

Renaissance Nusa Dua is cateres to more lifestyle oriented hotel with different theme in each of properties. This Nusa Dua one, took the theme of Traditional Balinese Theatre. 

This property may not have view like other Renaissance in Uluwatu, the sea view is also not really a sea view like in a beach front property. I’d say it’s just a glimpse. However, it’s still pretty nice. They do have a beach club which is shared with Courtyard Nusa Dua. 

Anyway, below is my verdict: 

1. The lobby is nice with open air concept and plenty of sofas and table, perfect to meet up with your friends or colleagues. With R Bar close to the lobby, the lobby will definitely impress visitors. Thank you for Mbak Risa who took care of my check-in process, all very smooth and fast. I checked-in early and my late checkout request also confirmed. 

2. Room is nice and spacious with a quirky design. Love the lighting design. The bathtub placement might be a bit awkward especially if you have a roommate, but thank God closeted shower and toilet are exist here. I had some issues trying to figure out lighting switches, but got used to it on the second day. The turndown service is small but super nice touch. The room ambassador done a great job making sure everything is spotless. Thank you Edrie and Novi.

3. Backstage restaurant, the whole industrial design is nice BUT I’m not a fan of the graffiti word artwork. The breakfast spread out all over the places, it can be hectic, and a lot of guests, but fortunately still under control with plenty of seats to choose from. Breakfast foods have a lot of variety and options, but my usual go to breakfast is the salad bar, fruits, juices, jamu, egg benedict, some traditional pancakes, and ice cream. Coffee is great to but it takes a while to get. I tried some menu for lunch/dinner such as gado-gado, baby octopus salad, and bintang battered fish burger. They are all good and has decent presentation (except the baby octopus salad, need better presentation). Cocktails, plenty of options to choose. I also recommend to try the Periodic Table in Atomic17 pool bar.

4. Staffs are amazing. From front officer, housekeeping, security, restaurants, pool side bar, everyone is so nice, friendly and accommodating. 

5. NO TAXI SCAMS unlike the other Ren in Uluwatu. I’m glad Grab Car, Go Car, Blue Bird etc. can go in without any dramas ;)

Okay, now what’s not so good: 

1. Mind you that this property also can host some events, so maybe it can be loud if there’s an event going on. Also the elevator is kinda small, cramp, and hot. Definitely need to improve the airflow in the elevator. 

2. The snacks before meal at the backstage restaurant is a hit and miss. Some of the crackers feel old, not crisps anymore, and don’t taste good anymore. You may need to check the crackers, make sure it’s fresh and crunchy!

3. I wonder what kind of chemical you’re using to disinfect the furniture especially in the backstage restaurants? It seems leaving a mark on my pants, yes I can get rid of the mark, but oh my…the smell took a few washes to fully get rid of it. 

Anyway, this is still a recommended property. I hope the management can improve it especially on some food presentation and snacks, apply some noise policy for events, elevator situation, and that chemical stuff you’re using.
title: Very close to perfect 5 stars.

text:
We stayed in Ren nusa dua twice, last year and this year. Unfortunately some guest handling and front desk experience was very different. Actually this review might be very biased because last year‘s stay was flawless and personalized. Note that last year I stayed as a Gold member, and this year I came as titanium hence I have higher expectations upon returning this year.

2023 review: 

- Pre arrival & arrival: We called a few days prior to arrival to ask whether they have big events (ie: wedding, corporate etc) planned during our stay. Front desk said no. Imagine our surprise upon arrival when we saw a big wedding banner. We just left and spend the day outside to avoid unnecessary drama. When we arrived back at the hotel, we found out they also have another event planned on the 3rd day of our stay. 

- Food: This is where they still shine, 10/10 for the F&B. Breakfast still one of the best in Bali. It‘s buffet but the quality is gourmet. The highlight for me is the dim sum (home made by Lion X team), juice bar and dessert bar. They recently opened 2 new restaurants, Lion X and Tanah Liat. Staffs were all very hospitable and always made sure we got what we need, from Chef Made and Andrew Christy at Backstage, Mba Irani and Chef Alex at Lion X. Lion X treated us to delicious dinner which was very generous. Valentine dinner experience by Chef Alit in Tanah Liat was good value. F&B team organized crowd from big events and main guests like a pro. In the end we feel little to no effect from the crowd in breakfast. Andrew took the time to inform us where and what time these events will take place in the hotel so we can plan the day accordingly.

- Room cleaning: Shoutout to Mba Ade, who meticulously arranged my clothes and skincare, cleaned my room, and put flowers in my bath tub for valentine‘s day.

- Elite benefits: another marriott property where you have to hustle for your benefits 1) Titanium benefits is a choice between different welcome snacks/drinks, free breakfast, or extra 1000 points. 2) While i understand 4 pm checkout in resort properties is based on availability, the night shift front desk showed discomfort when I asked for it. The first answer I got when I asked for late checkout availability was „checkout is at 12 pm“. I pushed a bit and he said „we only have 6 suites available, tomorrow we have arrival so let me check“. In the end I got 2 pm checkout, which is not a problem, but this pushback and interaction is unexpected for a marriott property in Asia. 3) Upgrade: upon check in we saw there is a studio suite available on the app so we asked for an enhanced upgrade. After pushing a bit FD agreed to upgrade us for half of our stay which was nice.

The difference can be really stark when you compare other marriott properties in Bali where front desk staffs are champions for elite members (ie: Westin Ubud, Aloft, Laguna, W to name a few).

————————————————————————-

2022 review:

World class bonvoyy stay experience. Faultless from start to finish.

- Service: this is way beyond typical Renaissance service, staffs are very friendly and helpful. They customize your stay preference and you feel very taken care of. One of my highlight was when my husband had vertigo at night and staff offered custom herbal drink for him and made sure we had all amenities needed for his condition.
- Food: Everyday we look forward to breakfast, lunch, dinner. Some of the menu are very creative, I also love the different Indonesian menu they offered. Chef Denny always ensure everything went perfect and menu are customized to our preference
- Spa: spa & massage were ok, i’ve had better massages at other places in Bali but the highlight was the facial (they offer top notch oxygen and biologique recherche facial).
- Private beach: transfer service is very prompt and comfortable but beach itself left much to be desired due to trash and sellers constantly approaching you.

text:
Our stay at Renaissance Bali Nusa Dua Resort has been nothing short of excellent. It was our first time travelling since the pandemic, and expectations for the trip had been sky-high. However, Renaissance not only met our expectations, but exceeded them greatly. It was a five-star experience from start to finish.

The hotel itself is relatively new, and opened its doors right before COVID. Much of the construction is spacious and open-concept, giving visitors a good view of the surrounding nature. The room we stayed in had a clear view of the sea, and in the afternoons we could even nap on the balcony under the soft breeze. Amenities-wise, Renaissance has just about everything a traveller needs. The rooms were spick and span, toiletries well-stocked, room service prompt; the hotel had a gym complete with towels and free juice post-workout, as well as spa facilities, bars, and a few swimming pools. The service at each of these places was impeccable; all of the staff were prompt and sincere, especially Wulan (who helmed the front desk), and we were even given free buggy rides to and from the spa, which was about only a four-minute walk from the main lobby.

Renaissance also wowed us with its dining facilities. In particular, three of them stand out. The Backstage Food Theatre serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner and we frequented it throughout our stay. The breakfast buffet spread had an excellent variety of pastries and dishes, comprising both Continental and local delights — most notably their crêpes and cappuccinos, which were made on the spot by staff. Both lunch and dinner menus, similarly, boasted an amazing selection, and we were spoilt for choice between sushi pizza and lobster bruschetta (we ended up ordering both!).

R Bar, adjacent to the main lobby, serves drinks and finger food throughout the day and up till midnight. The bartenders were incredibly courteous, providing us with ample recommendations and suggestions, and making sure we were always attended to. The highlight for us, however, had to be the newly-opened Tanah Liat, a fine-dining experience unmatched by anything on our trip. Tanah Liat served a delectable array of seafood and plant-based courses in the style of molecular gastronomy; we had, among other dishes, black cod and sea urchin, and it is no exaggeration to say that the restaurant ranks among one of the very best on all fronts: ambience, aesthetic, presentation, quality of food, and service.

We would like to specially acknowledge Christopher Smith, the Director of Operations at Renaissance. Throughout our stay at the hotel, Chris was incredibly helpful and friendly, offering assistance and making our already good impression of Renaissance an even better one. We had checked in slightly later than expected, at about 7pm, and Chris was at the lobby, patiently attending to us and offering various recommendations that greatly enriched our itinerary. Thanks, Chris!

It was an utmost pleasure staying at Renaissance Bali Nusa Dua Resort, and we highly recommend this hotel to anyone travelling through Bali, whether for work or for leisure. We will definitely be back!
title: A fantastic resort!! One of the best!!

text:
We stayed 2 nights in early June 2022. Family with two young kids. 
Only one wing was open and some parts of the resort was still under construction - however this did not impact our stay at all (not noisy or dusty, and all amenities were available for use). 

STAFF - Hands down one of the friendliest service we received during our 3 week stay in Bali.  Our travel style is to change hotels every 2-3 nights (mostly 5 star, occasionally 4.5 star) so we definitely had enough comparison.  Staff friendliness at Renaissance Nusa Dua was comparable to Four Seasons Jimbaran. We stayed at The Apurva Kempinski afterwards, but staff friendliness level was only half that of Renaissance. 
Everyone greeted you with genuine smiles and chats.  For example, we mistakenly thought a few of the Backstage restaurant waiters to be the Manager because of the sincerity and level of service (I think we saw the real Manager once who had no issue clearing plates off our table so we mistook him for just a nice waiter...haha). 

FOOD - So tasty, and price reasonable.  We had breakfast, lunch and dinner there.  Breakfast spread was amazing. Our kids loved the different types of cutlery and dinnerware presented to them each meal.  Only Backstage restaurant was open during our stay; but look forward to trying out their other restaurants (still getting ready) on our next trip. 

KIDS CLUB - The kids club layout itself is more targeted to younger kids (toddlers/preschool), probably not much for primary+ kids to do there.  We felt a bit uneasy about only one staff member manning the kids club (not many kids, but in case of emergency if something were to happen to that staff member...better to have two staff.)  BUT, the staff (Karina and one other lady) were AMAZING! They were so kind and enthusiastic - our kids fell in love.  They rated Renaissance kids club as their favourite out of this whole Bali trip because of the staff and the activities they enjoyed together (crafts, aqua aerobics etc).  Thank you. 

POOLS - the vibe at this hotel was great even though it was quite empty during our stay.  The music was good, staff were fun and encouraged you to try different things.  The multiple pools were all very different and enjoyable to swim in. 

BEACH CLUB - The hotel is not in front of a beach, but they offer free shuttle service in the form of private cars to the hotel's designated beach club area.  Shuttle service was okay (drivers weren't hotel staff, but outsourced I believe).  We arrived at beach around 11am, and the beach itself was filthy with rubbish which was really disappointing.  We saw someone starting to clean it up closer to midday but it was only half clean even then (we were worried our children would step on something sharp or play with something dirty/dangerous).  The worst part though were the local vendors who try to sell you things.  As soon as we got there, despite us repeatedly saying we weren't interested today, many of them took turns to aggressively sell one after another multiple times during our short stay at the beach club.  The hotel staff member at the beach club was friendly, but did not do anything to stop the vendors which I think the hotel should look into doing.  I understand (and do) supporting locals is important - but I don't really want to be buying sarong after sarong and paintings when I really don't need any more of it.  It totally ruined our experience there, and we did not bother to return to the beach club.  Also they only sold drinks at the beach club and no snacks/food. 

All in all, we loved Renaissance and look forward to revisiting on our next trip to see the resort in all its glory when they fully open.  Hopefully their staff friendliness levels remain the same even when they become more busier - because it is really to the merit of Renaissance Nusa Dua.  Thank you for a memorable stay.
title: Family friendly / Amazing staff friendliness / Fantastic food

text:
This hotel was recently soft-launched in Dec 2021, and yet havent made their grand opening.  Initial plan was to stay 2 nights, but after staying one night, I made impulsive decision to extend another 2 nights. I was having hard time to spot any flaws from this hotel, so here are notes for staying experience at Renaissance Nusa Dua:

1. Room 10/10 - new, modern,clean  spacious, and comfortable bed. Room has unique movie setting ambience with all ornaments to every detail attention.

2. Service 10/10 - Warm hospitality and service attitude are very genuine and felt in entire premises. All staffs in restaurant, gym, spa, pool, reception, lobby are very generous in giving their smile and nice gesture. Special thanks to Andrew, Nova, Prima, Jordi, Intan, Yuli from F&B crew. All  are outstanding

3. Breakfast 10/10 - Food and drinks choices are so extensive and of course they come with freshness and good taste satisfying every pallates. Fresh juices and almond milk are highlight to me.

4. Facilities 10/10 - With 4 huge pools, everyone gets their own space to lounge and relax at the pools. Gym has complete equipments and nice fresh smell. They also provide free bicycle to lend.

5. Spa 10/10 - They have sauna and steam room in addition to relaxing whirlpool. Had massage treatment at the spa, it was rejuvenating experience.

6. Location 9/10 - The hotel does not have direct access to the beach, but they provide free shuttle to private beach, or you can ride bike for just 2kms.

7. Restaurant 10/10 - Had all meals- breakfast,lunch, afternoon tea, and dinne- in house during entire stay. All foods are so good and top notch in presentation.

Will definitely re-stay here when in Nusa Dua and highly recommend this place to explore Nusa Dua.

text:
The location is outside the ITDC Nusa Dua area and in an alley. This hotel has just opened in December 2021 and only 100 rooms are available of a total of 400 rooms. was given 2 room cards and a purple welcome drink from pea flower. Because I had babymoon request, they provide congratulation letter and slice cake (the size is big and delicious, triple chocolate cake with macaroon topping). 

When you enter the room, a light on the floor with a Balinese dancer motif presented. Room with modern interior accented with wood, gray and light blue m with balcony equipped with sofa bed and table with twin bed size 140x200. Inside the wardrobe there is a laundry bag, kimono, iron, shoe polish. There is a coffee table with 2 working chairs. a lot of plugs in the room. TV size 55 inches with clear TV channels. Wifi is smooth and fast. notes and ballpoint pen are also provided. Hygiene kits are also provided which contain 2 masks, 2 wet tissues and 1 hand sanitizer. The drinking water brand is Aqua Reflection and free refill, the tea sachet is brew me with 4 variants and renaissance drip coffee. 
The bathroom has a sink, bathtub, separate closet and shower. For the shower there is a handshower and a rain shower. Closet uses an ecowasher. Amenities are provided with a toothbrush, comb and frezza mouthwash, amenities use Tokyo milk. The filling of the bathtub is fast but the water pressure in the shower is a bit low. The bathroom also includes a hair dryer and a magnifying mirror with lamp. Towels are provided each for the body towel, hand towel and face towel.
Their lobby is colorful with lots of seating both sofas and armchairs. There are 3 swimming pools, the main pool, jungle pool and kids pool. there is a kids club which operates every 8am to 8pm and they provide a different schedule of activities every day. Inside the kidspool there is a fairly complete play area, there are also outdoor games but it is quite hot (especially during the day). The restaurant is quite spacious and has lots of artwork and an interesting interior that combines graffiti and retro. Gym and spa location is in a separate building very far from the main building. The gym itself operates 24 hours. The equipment are many and complete. They served guava juice and bottled orange juice were available. There is also a sauna and Jacuzzi. They have a beach in Nusa Dua which is 4 km from the hotel. They provide free shuttle. On the beach they provide free drinks per guest with a choice of soft drinks or mineral water. That night we tried dinner at a restaurant. We ordered Black ink fetuccine and Taliwang Grilled Chicken. The taste is very tasty and fits our tongue. 

The breakfast location is in the "backstage" restaurant. Available variants 1. Beverage section (fresh, healthy, chilled juice, coffee and tea, yogurt, fresh and sliced fruit, yogurt (mango, coconut, almond) 2. Bakery Pastry (almond, tart, sourdough, croissant(almond, tiramisu, chocolate, plain). 3. Western (bebek betutu signature egg benedict, classic egg benedict, streaky bacon, beef bacon, sausage (pork, beef, chicken), baked bean, omellete, tomato, creamy mushroom, eggplant parmigiana, hashbrown). 4. Asian (fried rice, fried noodles, dumplings and dumplings, Noodle station). 5. Indian (bread pakora, aloo gobi mutter, tofu tempeh curry). 6. Bali (chicken pelalah, vegetable urap) 7. Dessert (ice cream with sandwich/burger, ice cream roll, waffle, pancake, injin porridge, bread butter pudding, pandan popsicle, panna cotta, candy) The ice cream flavors are matcha, coconut, mocha, strawberry, chocolate, vanilla, banana. 
While jogging, I found a lot of caterpillars on the jogging track, I told the receptionist at check-out, they had actually been noted, and had extra pest control to get rid of the caterpillars

text:
3泊4日、朝食付のプランで滞在しました。総合的にとても素晴らしいホテルでした。特にスタッフの方々がフレンドリーで親切です。

DPS空港からはホテルのサービスで送迎を依頼。(35kRp＋＋かかる約3500円に21%の税金とサービス料)
空港の出口でルネサンスのボードをかかげた運転手が待っててくれます。綺麗なホンダ車には瓶の水、消毒用のティッシュが用意されていました。
支払いは宿泊と合わせて引かれるのでキャッシュは不要です。送迎はおそらく業務委託。

ホテル到着後はウェルカムドリンクがもらえます。少し甘いうっすらピンク色の不思議な水。
ランチ、ディナー、スパ(60分)、アフタヌーンティーを各1回ずつのバウチャーをもらえました。どれも素晴らしいサービス。ちなみにスパは時間帯を指定して予約できます。

■部屋
とても広く清潔感がありました。バスタブ付でシャワー、トイレは別。シャワーの水圧は弱め。
トイレは少し流れづらいですが、2回目くらいで流れてくれます。
アメニティには黒のビーチサンダルがついていました。その他ボディウォッシュ、シャンプーリンス、カミソリなど一通り揃っています。ドライヤーの風量がすごい強くていい。ドリンクはコーヒーと水と紅茶。
電源はUSBが一口ついているので変圧器はあってもなくても大丈夫でした。
ベランダにはソファとテーブルがあるので外も楽しめます。

■食事
朝食はビュッフェで中華、インドネシア料理、インターナショナル(オムレツとかベーコンとか)から好きなものを好きなだけチョイスできる。クレープ、ヌードル、オムレツはその場で作ってくれました。

ランチとディナーは前菜、メイン、デザートと分かれており好きなものを注文。ナシゴレンがとても美味しかった。

■サービス
何も言っていないのに誕生日であることを知り、ルームサービスでチョコレートケーキとメッセージカードを届けてくれました。

毎日11時頃にクリーニングスタッフが来てくれて水やタオルの補充も快く受けてくれました。

ジム、サウナ、スパは少し歩いたところにありますがタクシーを手配してくれます。タクシーだと1分もかからず着くので歩きのほうがいいと思います。
ジム利用は無料でタオル、イヤホン、水、ジュースが常備されていました。
サウナ、スチームバス、ジャグジーが無料。利用の際は鍵付きロッカーが利用できました。
プールではタオルの貸し出し、ベッドやパラソルもあり快適に過ごせます。
スパはバウチャーを利用すれば60分で全身両面が無料。サービスでここまでしてくれることは日本ではないでしょう。力加減も雰囲気もよくスッキリしました。

■その他
ATMがあり300,000Rpからキャッシングできました。細かいお金はフロントで両替できましたが、細かいお札のストックが無いこともあるようです。
たまに施設内に猫がいます。
虫は少なからずいますが、スタッフが床掃除を頻繁にしてくれているので助かります。部屋にはほぼいなかったです。
title: とても素晴らしいホテル

저는 패키지로 숙박해서 식당을 이용할 기회가 많았습니다. 피자, 햄버거, 핫도그 등 웨스턴 음식은 다 맛있었습니다.  red ruby 라는 디저트는 제가 발리에서 먹은 가장 맛있는 음식중 하나입니다.:) 
그리고 조식은 특별했습니다. 저는 여러 리조트를 옮겨다녀서 조식이 다 뻔하게 느껴졌는데 이 리조트의 조식은 새로웠습니다. 에그베네딕트 조차도 바질을 넣어 평범하지 않게 만들었습니다. 하나같이 예쁘고 맛도 좋았습니다. 셰프님이 맛은 어떤지 항상 물어보며 고객들의 반응을 살핍니다. 
로비에서 애프터눈티도 먹었는데 비주얼이 아름답고 맛있었습니다. suli 라는 친절한 직원분이 숙박객의 만족도에 관심을 많이 가지고 있는거 같아 인상깊고 감사했습니다. 리셉션 직원들 빼고는 모든 직원이 정말 친절하고 프로페셔널합니다. 수영장, 조식당에 나타나는 송충이인지 지네인지 벌레만 없애주세요. 너무 무섭습니다..:(
시설이 너무 좋고 멋진 리조트입니다.

누사두아에 신규 오픈한 리조트답게
전체적으로 최상의 컨디션을 자랑!
직원들의 의상도 멋지고 응대도 쿨 함
감각적인 인테리어로 모든 공간이 포토존!
히지만 F&B는 우리부부 기준 SoSo 

<객실> 
현시점 객실이 모두 오픈된게 아니라​
디럭스 가든, 디럭스 씨뷰 만 오픈되있음
- 좁지않은 객실과 발코니는 아주 나이쓰
- 가구들이 매우 고급짐
- 침구류는 역시 쌔거 티 팍팍나게 뽀송함
- 화장실 및 샤워실도 깔끔
- 전체적인 룸 컨디션은 최상
- 객실에서 보이는 바다는 너무 아름다움
- 르네상스 클러치백이 너무 탐나서 사진 백번찍음
아주 만족한 룸 컨디션!
신규호텔이 안좋을 순 없긴하다고 생각했지만
이정도로 좋을줄은 몰랐음
 
<F&B>
세끼를 먹었지만 르네상스 누사두아의 F&B는 
우리부부 입맛엔 SoSo이기에  많이 언급하지 않겠음
                     - 인도네시아 현지 입맛 특화
- 우리 부부의 입맛엔 간이 맞지않음
- 주문 후 조리시간이 매우 오래걸림
- 메뉴는 많지만 먹을게 많이 없음
 
<수영장>
총4개의 수영장 모두 너무 훌륭!
- 가족들이 놀 수 있는 키즈풀이 매우 나이쓰
- 메인풀에 있는 튜브는 물놀이하기에 재격
- 선베드와 방갈로는 너무 편안하고 관리가 잘됨
- 사진찍을 곳도 많고 너무 고급진 수영장 디자인
- 프라이빗 비치는 관리가 잘되어 너무 훌륭했고
상주하던 직원의 서비스는 너무 좋았음
